//! Structured error formatting and handling
//!
//! This module provides structured error formatting with errors going to stdout
//! in the same format as normal output, including actionable suggestions. Never lets
//! raw dependency output leak through. This enables agents to parse and act on
//! failures programmatically.
//!
//! ## Error Format Specification
//!
//! Structured errors follow this format:
//!
//! ```toon
//! error: <error_code>
//! message: <human_readable_message>
//! context:
//!   field: value
//! suggestions:
//!   - <actionable_suggestion_1>
//!   - <actionable_suggestion_2>
//! exit_code: <numeric_exit_code>
//! ```
//!
//! ## Example
//!
//! ```rust
//! use mytool::internal::errors::{StructuredError, ErrorFormatter, format_error};
//!
//! let error = StructuredError::new(
//!     "CONFIG_NOT_FOUND",
//!     "Configuration file not found",
//!     exit_code::EXIT_CONFIG,
//! )
//! .with_context("path", "/path/to/config.toml")
//! .with_suggestion("Run 'mytool --install' to create a default configuration");
//!
//! let formatted = format_error(&error, OutputFormat::Toon).unwrap();
//! println!("{}", formatted);
//! ```

